Habitat:
This species occurs in a wide range of habitats, from well preserved streams (
Fig. 63
) to temporary pools with moderately polluted waters (
Fig. 60
). This successful species favours margins of lowland habitats with clear water, muddy bottom and high exposure to the sun. In one locality (San Miguel de Parada) the water temperature reached 36ºC at midday.
